        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 6:19PM EDT by NWS Wakefield VA</headline>
        <description>At 619 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Boydton, or 10 miles south of Chase City, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph, heavy rain, and frequent
lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Reduced visibility and minor flooding
possible. Frequent cloud to ground lightning strikes.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Boydton around 625 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Beechwood, Bracey,
Keats, Finchley, John H Kerr Dam, Eppes Fork, John H Kerr Reservoir,
Baskerville, and Skipwith.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
